          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to compute a specific value related to gas therm factors. Scalar functions return a single value, which can be used in queries wherever expressions are allowed. This function performs calculations based on input parameters to determine a therm factor, which is a measure used in the energy industry to convert gas volume to energy content."
